-- Unipetrol Declines Most in Three Months on Refinery Shutdown
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-02T14:12:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/unipetrol-declines-most-in-three-months-on-refinery-shutdown.html
Unipetrol AS (UNIP) , the largest Czech
refiner, fell the most in more than three months after saying it
will discontinue production at its Paramo unit.  The shares dropped 1.9 percent to 167.70 koruna by 4:05
p.m. in  Prague , the biggest decline on a closing basis since
March 29.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
